   "source": [
    "### 2.3.1. Yeo-Johnson transformation\n",
    "\n",
    "As the RFM variables, especially Recency and Monetary, exhibit strong positive skewness, the Yeo-Johnson transformation is employed to improve distributional symmetry and enhance the suitability of the data for distance-based clustering methods such as K-Means.\n",
    "\n",
    "Although a logarithmic transformation could also reduce skewness, the Yeo–Johnson transformation was selected because it estimates the optimal power transformation from the data, often producing more normally distributed features without requiring manual specification of the transformation."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
