    "However, this improvement in compactness comes at the cost of reduced cluster separation. The **Silhouette Score** decreases by approximately **24.7%** (from **0.3319** to **0.2501**), suggesting that the resulting clusters are less cohesive and less clearly separated. Similarly, the **Calinski–Harabasz Index** decreases by approximately **26.3%** (from **492.79** to **362.98**), indicating a weaker balance between within-cluster compactness and between-cluster separation.\n",
